---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../../../styles/global.css';
export const prerender = true;
---

<Layout title="SEO at Scale — How We Deployed 1000+ Pages in 30 Days | xSoft Blog" description="The content strategy, automation tools, and technical SEO architecture behind deploying over 1,000 indexed pages on a single site within 8 weeks of launch." keywords="SEO at scale, content automation, structured data, Astro SEO, Google indexing, 1000 pages">

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "SEO at Scale — How We Deployed 1000+ Pages in 30 Days",
    "description": "The content strategy and automation behind deploying 1,000+ indexed pages within 8 weeks of launch.",
    "datePublished": "2026-07-15",
    "dateModified": "2026-07-15",
    "author": { "@type": "Person", "name": "Raj Naik", "url": "https://www.xsoftlimited.com/about/" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "xSoft Ltd", "logo": { "@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://www.xsoftlimited.com/social-card.svg" } },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.xsoftlimited.com/blog/seo-at-scale-1000-pages/" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How do you create 1000+ SEO pages without duplicate content?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Each page targets a unique long-tail keyword with custom content generated using AI with human editorial oversight. We use visual enhancement recipes (callout blocks, stat strips, comparison cards) to ensure every page has unique visual structure, not just unique text." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How long does it take Google to index 1000 pages?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "With proper technical SEO (XML sitemap, internal linking, structured data), Google indexed 744 of our 1000+ pages within 8 weeks of launch. Key factors: fast TTFB (<100ms), no crawl errors, and fresh content signals via dateModified." }},
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What structured data should every page have?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "At minimum: Article schema (for blog posts), FAQPage schema (3+ Q&A per page), and BreadcrumbList. These qualify your pages for rich snippets in Google search results, significantly improving click-through rates." }}
    ]
  })} />

  <section class="pt-10 pb-8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-indigo-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">SEO at Scale</span>
      </nav>

      <article class="prose prose-invert max-w-none">
        <div class="mb-8">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
            <span class="px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs bg-emerald-500/10 text-emerald-400 border border-emerald-500/20">SEO</span>
            <span class="px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs bg-emerald-500/10 text-emerald-400 border border-emerald-500/20">Content</span>
            <span class="px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs bg-emerald-500/10 text-emerald-400 border border-emerald-500/20">Automation</span>
          </div>
          <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-black text-white leading-tight">SEO at Scale — 1000 Pages in 30 Days</h1>
          <div class="mt-4 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
            <time datetime="2026-07-15">15 July 2026</time>
            <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
            <span>7 min read</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-8">On ScrabbleWordsFinder.com, we went from zero to 744 indexed pages in 8 weeks. Here's the strategy, the automation, and the technical decisions that made it possible — without sacrificing quality.</p>

        <!-- The Strategy -->
        <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-emerald-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-emerald-400 pl-4">The Strategy: Topical Clusters</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">We didn't create 1,000 random pages. We built <strong>topical clusters</strong> — groups of related content that establish authority on a subject. Google rewards depth over breadth.</p>

        <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-emerald-500/30 bg-emerald-950/10">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
            <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-emerald-400">15+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Categories</p></div>
            <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-emerald-400">1,000+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Pages</p></div>
            <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-emerald-400">744</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Indexed (8 weeks)</p></div>
            <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-emerald-400">58%</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Index Rate</p></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Each category has a <strong>landing page</strong> (pillar content) that links to all posts in the cluster. Posts cross-link to each other. This creates a dense internal link graph that Google's crawler follows efficiently.</p>

        <!-- Content Generation -->
        <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-emerald-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-emerald-400 pl-4">Content Generation Pipeline</h2>

        <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 Our Pipeline</p>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Keyword research:</span> Identify long-tail queries with search volume using topic analysis</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">AI content generation:</span> Generate initial drafts using LLMs with topic-specific prompts</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Visual enhancement:</span> Apply FVT (Full Visual Treatment) — callouts, stat strips, card grids, comparison blocks</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">4</span>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SEO infrastructure:</span> Auto-inject JSON-LD schemas, meta tags, cross-links, and FAQ sections</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">5</span>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Quality scoring:</span> Automated line-count audit — pages below 180 lines are flagged for expansion</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Technical SEO -->
        <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-emerald-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-emerald-400 pl-4">Technical SEO Essentials</h2>

        <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-emerald-500/20 bg-emerald-950/10">
            <p class="text-emerald-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Sub-100ms TTFB</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Cloudflare Workers serve pages from the nearest edge location. No origin server latency.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-emerald-500/20 bg-emerald-950/10">
            <p class="text-emerald-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Trailing slash consistency</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">trailingSlash: 'always' — no duplicate content from /page vs /page/.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-emerald-500/20 bg-emerald-950/10">
            <p class="text-emerald-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">XML Sitemap</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Auto-generated with lastmod dates. Submitted to Google Search Console.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-emerald-500/20 bg-emerald-950/10">
            <p class="text-emerald-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Canonical URLs</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Every page has a self-referencing canonical. Prevents parameter-based duplicates.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-emerald-500/20 bg-emerald-950/10">
            <p class="text-emerald-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Structured Data</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Article + FAQPage + BreadcrumbList on every blog post. Validates in Rich Results Test.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-emerald-500/20 bg-emerald-950/10">
            <p class="text-emerald-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Internal Linking</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Automated cross-link injection: every new post gets 2 inbound links from related pages.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Automation Tools -->
        <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-emerald-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-emerald-400 pl-4">Automation Tools We Built</h2>

        <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800/30">
            <p class="text-white font-semibold text-sm mb-1">CHOP (Content Harvest & Optimise Pipeline)</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Batch creates and optimises blog posts — generates content, applies visual treatment, injects schemas, and cross-links in one command.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800/30">
            <p class="text-white font-semibold text-sm mb-1">SEO Health Check</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Automated audit that validates every page against thresholds — title length, description length, schemas, content word count, and internal links.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800/30">
            <p class="text-white font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Prettify (Full Visual Treatment)</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Transforms plain text pages into rich visual content — adds stat strips, callout blocks, comparison cards, step lists, and cross-link panels.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800/30">
            <p class="text-white font-semibold text-sm mb-1">BlogCrossLinks</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Reusable component that auto-injects contextual links to related tools and pages at the top of every blog post, boosting internal link equity.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800/30">
            <p class="text-white font-semibold text-sm mb-1">Build & Deploy Pipeline</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Automated release train — build, migrate databases, deploy to staging, run tests, then promote to live. Three environments with isolated data.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800/30">
            <p class="text-white font-semibold text-sm mb-1">add-sources-section.py</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Injects a Sources & References block with hyperlinked citations before the author section.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800/30">
            <p class="text-white font-semibold text-sm mb-1">check-orphaned-pages.mjs</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Finds pages with zero inbound links (SEO orphans) so they can be connected to the link graph.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-800/30">
            <p class="text-white font-semibold text-sm mb-1">generate_seo_sql.py</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Syncs Google Search Console data with a local seo_index table for tracking index status.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- CTA -->
        <div class="not-prose mt-12 p-6 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-950/30 to-green-950/20 border border-emerald-500/30 text-center">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">Want this for your site?</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-400">We build SEO content pipelines that scale. From technical setup to content generation.</p>
          <a href="/contact/" class="mt-4 inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 rounded-xl bg-indigo-600 hover:bg-indigo-500 text-white font-semibold transition-all">
            Discuss Your SEO Strategy →
          </a>
        </div>

        <aside class="not-prose border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
          <div class="grid gap-3">
            <a href="/blog/building-rag-chatbots-cloudflare/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-indigo-500/50 transition-all group">
              <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
              <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-400">Building RAG Chatbots on Cloudflare</span>
            </a>
            <a href="/blog/cloudflare-d1-vs-kv/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-indigo-500/50 transition-all group">
              <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
              <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-400">Cloudflare D1 vs KV — When to Use What</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </aside>

        <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
          <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-indigo-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
